# ── GC-1 · the derived causal event poset N = (Ev, ≼), READ-SIDE ONLY ──────────────────────────
# OBJECT:    the spine — a derived index over the audited stores' append events, under the causal
#            order generated by g1 (per-store append chains) ∪ g2 (reads-from references) ∪ g3
#            (recorded program order). dn-global-event-clock §2.1 (GC-N1), §2.2 (generators+audit).
# INVARIANT: read-side derivation, never a write-side sequencer (§2.1-1, the zone-separation
#            argument); metadata-only rows (§2.7 GC-N8 — event id / store / stratum / position /
#            reference ids; NO payload, NO note text, NO observation body — ever); wall-clock is
#            NEVER a generator (Law C4 — no ts/created_at column is read as an ordering key);
#            acyclicity is a construction invariant, not an assumption (§2.8-1, fail-closed).
# ENFORCED:  structural — the spine holds no store write handle (it SELECTs through live read
#            connections and returns data), no model, opens no socket; `derive()` runs a Kahn
#            topological sort and raises `SpineCycleError` on any cycle (a corrupted/forged
#            reference = an integrity failure). Pure-core, ops/derived-tier, ∉ MIRROR_READABLE.
"""The global event clock N as a derived causal spine (GC-1, dn-global-event-clock §2.1–§2.8).

N is the pair `(Ev, ≼)`: all **store-append events** across the audited stores, under the causal
order that is the reflexive-transitive closure of three generator families (note §2.2):

  * **g1 — per-store append chains.** Each store's own append order, where the store records one.
    Ordered by rowid / version_seq — NEVER by a wall timestamp (Law C4: `created_at`/`started_at`/
    `at`/`timestamp` decorate events for display only; they generate no order).
  * **g2 — reads-from (content-address references).** An event whose row records an identifier
    MINTED by another event is causally after it. This is the attestation auto-link
    (`core/attestation/attestor.py:59-69`, `store.producers_of`) GENERALIZED from attested actions
    to all store events; the attestation DAG embeds as-is (the calibration oracle, §2.8-5).
    Faithfully implementing §2.8-5: an attestation is a proof-layer record, NOT the minter of its
    outputs (each output is written to a store, whose OWN event mints it), so attestation→
    attestation order is exactly the `derived_from_ids` DAG — never the raw output/input hash
    coincidence, which over-generates on a SHARED corpus/config digest (mutable state listed as
    both an input and an output of many attestations) and would manufacture a false cycle.
  * **g3 — recorded program order.** Where one actor's sequence is itself recorded — a run's
    `start_run → add_claim*` (`core/stores/runledger.py`).

**Soundness and incompleteness, stated as a law (note §2.2 — carried verbatim).** Every derived
edge is true (`≼_derived ⊆ ≼_true` — g1 by the single-writer discipline, g2 by content-address
unforgeability, g3 by the recording actor's own order). The converse fails: an unrecorded flow (a
model read a note and influenced a later artifact without a citation) leaves no edge, so **derived
concurrency over-approximates true concurrency**. Every consumer of N inherits this caveat.

Per store, `≼` restricts to a total chain; globally it is a genuine partial order, and that
partiality is a feature (recorded concurrency), not a deficiency (GC-N1).

The audit of what the stores actually record (note §2.2, verified on disk 2026-07-16):

  | store        | g1 chain form                         | how it enters Ev                   |
  |--------------|---------------------------------------|------------------------------------|
  | versions     | per-doc chains by `version_seq`       | g1 (per doc) + produces `digest`   |
  | run ledger   | runs: rowid chain; claims: g3         | g1(runs)+g3(run→claims)+g2(support)|
  | edges        | rowid chain                           | g1 + g2 via `(u, v)` atom digests  |
  | derived      | g2 DAG (`derived_from`) — see below   | g2 only (NO rowid g1 chain)        |
  | attestations | rowid chain PLUS the g2 DAG           | g1 + g2 (`derived_from_ids`/hashes)|
  | eval results | NONE (DuckDB, keyed only)             | chain-less; g2 via key/evidence    |
  | catalog      | NONE (keyed by path)                  | chain-less; produces `digest` (g2) |

**Why the derived store is g2-only (a deliberate, grounded exception).** `DerivedStore.add` uses
`INSERT OR REPLACE`, which REASSIGNS rowid on the idempotent re-write of an artifact. A re-recorded
PARENT can therefore land at a HIGHER rowid than its child, so a rowid g1 chain would contradict
the g2 `derived_from` edge and manufacture a spurious cycle on real (re-run) data. Note §2.2 pins
the derived order as "chain (ties broken by g2, never by wall)": the order IS the `derived_from`
DAG, which is content-id based and store-guaranteed acyclic (`DerivedStore._guard_acyclic`). So the
spine derives NO g1 chain for the derived store; its causal order is entirely g2.

Read-side ONLY: this module derives, and never writes back into, any source store. It holds no
model, opens no socket, and imports no network-capable path (the sealed-core import discipline is
unchanged). The Σ-gated order-query wrapper (GC-N8) is parked — the stratum TAG lands here so the
wrapper needs no re-derivation later; the tag is a per-store library default (see `_STRATUM`).

Not built here (non-goals, per plan §9): clock maps / p_κ / N_s laws (bp-053); cuts (bp-055); the
T-meet completion (bp-056); the Σ-gated query wrapper. This is the spine skeleton and nothing more.
"""

